HEADWORD: Oligarchy
<hw>Ol"i*gar"chy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Oligarchies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Gr. <?/;
<grk>'oli`gos</grk> few, little + <grk>'a`rchein</grk> to rule, govern:
cf. F. <ets>oligarchie</ets>.]</ety> <def>A form of government in which
the supreme power is placed in the hands of a few persons; also, those
who form the ruling few.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All <qex>oligarchies</qex>, wherein a few men domineer, do what
they list.</q> <rj><qau>Burton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oligist</ent>⟦br⟧
